{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\nAdopt the B1 batch primitive (`_store.batch_stage_and_commit`, ticket\n890d-4733-1c88-4976 â€” **hard prerequisite; this ticket is `depends_on` B1**) on the NDJSON\nimporter's independent passes so a bulk import commits `ceil(events/256)` commits instead\nof one-per-event.\n\n## Why\n`src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py` already has idempotency-by-`source_id` and deferred-push,\nbut each pass still funnels through a per-event commit. The write funnels differ by pass and\nseveral carry STATE-READING GUARDS that must still run â€” so this is NOT a blanket\n\"create_core/append_event variant\":\n- Pass 1 (CREATE) â†’ `rebar.create_ticket` â†’ `composer.create_core` â†’ `_seam.append_event`.\n- Pass 2a (parents) â†’ `edit_ticket(parent=â€¦)` â†’ composer/leaf edit path.\n- Pass 2b (links) â†’ `rebar.graph._links.add_dependency` â†’ `_write_link_event` â†’\n  `_seam.append_event`, guarded by cycle detection, hierarchy promotion, and idempotency\n  (`_is_active_link`) â€” those guards READ current state and MUST run before the event is\n  composed.\n- Pass 2c (file-impact / verify-commands) and Pass 2d (comments) â†’ `src/rebar/_commands/\n  leaf.py` (`set_file_impact` / `set_verify_commands` / comment), NOT `create_core`.\n\n## Scope\n- Introduce the compose/commit split at the **`_seam.append_event` layer** (the common\n  funnel): each command still runs its own state-reading guards and COMPOSES its event, but\n  instead of committing immediately it can RETURN the composed `(ticket_id, event_dict)` to\n  a caller-supplied buffer. Guards are preserved; only the final `git commit` is deferred.\n- In `src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py`, buffer composed events per independent pass (1, 2a,\n  2b, 2c, 2d) and flush each buffer through `batch_stage_and_commit` in chunks (default 256,\n  hard-coded â€” no new config key).\n- Pass 2e (statuses) is STATEFUL (children-before-parents, `cascade=False`) â†’ left\n  per-event, unchanged.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Compose/commit split at `_seam.append_event` (and the leaf/graph write funnels it fronts): a command can return its composed `(ticket_id, event_dict)` without committing, with all existing state-reading guards (link cycle/promotion/idempotency, edit validation) still run; the default committing path is unchanged for every non-importer caller\n- [ ] Importer Passes 1 + 2aâ€“2d buffer composed events and flush via `batch_stage_and_commit` in 256-event chunks; Pass 2e (statuses) remains per-event\n- [ ] A real import of a synthetic N-event NDJSON file (`import_tickets`) produces a real tickets branch with commit count == `ceil(N/256)` (proving command: `git -C <tracker> rev-list --count HEAD` before/after), and replays to state byte-identical to the per-event path\n- [ ] Idempotent re-import (source_id re-scan) still skips already-imported events (no duplicate events, no extra commits)\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && python -m pytest tests/ -k import -q` all green\n## Deferred-commit opt-in (mechanism)\nThe compose/commit split is OPT-IN via a new optional keyword arg on the `_seam.append_event`\nfunnel (and the leaf/graph write helpers that front it): `buffer: list[tuple[str, dict]] |\nNone = None`. When `buffer is None` (the default) behavior is EXACTLY as today â€” the event is\ncomposed AND committed â€” so **every existing caller is unchanged with no need to enumerate\nthem**. When a caller passes a `buffer`, the composed `(ticket_id, event_dict)` is appended to\nit and the immediate commit is skipped; the importer owns the buffer and flushes it via\n`batch_stage_and_commit`. State-reading guards (link cycle/promotion/idempotency, edit\nvalidation) run BEFORE the append in both modes.\n\n## Commit-count math (per-pass flush)\nThe importer flushes each independent pass's buffer separately, so total NEW commits =\n`sum_over_passes( ceil(pass_events / 256) )`, NOT `ceil(total/256)`. For a synthetic import of\nN=3000 tickets with 1 CREATE + 1 comment each (~3000 CREATE in pass 1, ~3000 COMMENT in pass\n2d), that is `ceil(3000/256) + ceil(3000/256) = 12 + 12 = 24` batch commits vs ~6000 per-event\ncommits (>=10x fewer). The benchmark asserts the **delta** (commits after import âˆ’ commits\nbefore import), since the tracker carries baseline commits from `init_repo`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783651440367311001,"uuid":"1fb2f897-2cca-4778-a814-8ff794a4068a"}